T3DB:
Organotins are endocrine
disruptors and are believed
to contribute to obesity
by inappropriate activation

receptor gamma, leading
to adipocyte differentiation.
(A184); Organotins inhibit
the chymotrypsin-like activity
of 20S and cellular proteasomes
by binding to the beta-5 subunit.
This results in apoptosis
caused by downstream effects
in the proteasome pathway.
(A181); Organotins are endocrine
disruptors and are believed
to contribute to obesity
by inappropriate activation
of retinoic acid receptors,
leading to adipocyte differentiation.
(A184); Tributyltin inhibits
thioredoxin reductase,
leading to hydrogen peroxide
production. (A185)
data.value: Organotins are endocrine disruptors and are believed to contribute to obesity by inappropriate activation of peroxisome proliferator-activated receptor gamma, leading to adipocyte differentiation. (A184); Organotins inhibit the chymotrypsin-like activity of 20S and cellular proteasomes by binding to the beta-5 subunit. This results in apoptosis caused by downstream effects in the proteasome pathway. (A181); Organotins are endocrine disruptors and are believed to contribute to obesity by inappropriate activation of retinoic acid receptors, leading to adipocyte differentiation. (A184); Tributyltin inhibits thioredoxin reductase, leading to hydrogen peroxide production. (A185)
